## Code Structure & Decomposition

### Hard Limits
- Single function: max **40 lines** (excluding comments)
- Single file: max **200 lines**
- Single component: max **100 lines** (JSX included)
- Nesting depth: max **3 levels**; extract early returns or subcomponents beyond that

### When to Extract a Function
Whenever a block of code meets any of these:
- Has a comment above it explaining what it does → it should be its own named function
- Used more than once → extract and reuse
- Can be described in one sentence → name it that way

### When to Split a File
- File exceeds 200 lines → split by responsibility
- Component has both data-fetching logic and rendering → split into container + presentational
- Multiple unrelated helpers in one file → separate into focused util files

### Naming Must Reflect Intent
\`\`\`ts
// ❌ Vague
const handle = async (data: any) => { ... }
const process = (input) => { ... }

// ✅ Descriptive
const handleReviewSubmit = async (rating: Rating) => { ... }
const calculateNextDueDate = (card: Card, rating: Rating) => { ... }
\`\`\`

### No Mega-Functions
\`\`\`ts
// ❌ Don't do this — one function doing everything
async function handleCardReview(cardId: string, rating: Rating) {
  const card = await prisma.card.findUnique(...)
  const f = fsrs()
  const result = f.next(card, new Date(), rating)
  await prisma.card.update(...)
  await prisma.reviewLog.create(...)
  revalidateTag("cards")
  // ... 60 more lines
}

// ✅ Decomposed
async function handleCardReview(cardId: string, rating: Rating) {
  const card = await getCardById(cardId)
  const scheduled = scheduleCard(card, rating)
  await saveReviewResult(cardId, scheduled)
  revalidateTag("cards")
}

async function getCardById(cardId: string) { ... }
function scheduleCard(card: Card, rating: Rating) { ... }
async function saveReviewResult(cardId: string, result: SchedulingInfo) { ... }
\`\`\`

### React Components
\`\`\`tsx
// ❌ One component with everything inside
export function ReviewPage() {
  // 200 lines of hooks, handlers, and JSX mixed together
}

// ✅ Split by concern
export function ReviewPage() {
  const { card, isLoading } = useCurrentCard()
  if (isLoading) return <ReviewSkeleton />
  return <ReviewLayout card={card} />
}

function ReviewLayout({ card }: { card: Card }) { ... }
function ReviewSkeleton() { ... }
\`\`\`

### Early Return over Deep Nesting
\`\`\`ts
// ❌ Arrow-shaped code
function processCard(card: Card | null) {
  if (card) {
    if (card.state === State.New) {
      if (card.reps === 0) {
        // actual logic buried here
      }
    }
  }
}

// ✅ Guard clauses
function processCard(card: Card | null) {
  if (!card) return null
  if (card.state !== State.New) return null
  if (card.reps !== 0) return null
  // actual logic at top level
}
\`\`\`

### Reminder for AI
When generating code:
1. Write the high-level function first (max 15 lines)
2. Extract each sub-step into a named helper
3. If you find yourself writing a comment to explain a block → extract it as a function instead
4. Prefer many small focused functions over one complete solution